    md("## 1. Why NumPy?\n\nPython lists are flexible but slow for numerical work because each element is a full Python object with overhead.\n\nNumPy stores elements in a **contiguous block of typed memory** — operations run in optimised C/Fortran under the hood.\n\n| Task | Python list | NumPy array |\n|------|-------------|-------------|\n| Sum 10 M numbers | ~0.5 s | ~0.01 s |\n| Element-wise multiply | requires loop | single expression |\n| Linear algebra | manual | built-in |\n\n> **Rule**: if you are writing a numeric loop in Python, there is almost certainly a NumPy one-liner for it."),
